Source: bulwark
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Viet Anh Nguyen <vietanh.dev@gmail.com>
# Launchpad builders have NO network access, so every crate is vendored into the
# source tarball (see scripts/build-ppa-source.sh) and the build runs with
# CARGO_NET_OFFLINE=true. Build-Depends therefore lists only the toolchain, not
# individual librust-* packages. `cargo`/`rustc` come from the target series'
# archive — verify the series' rustc is new enough for the dependency tree before
# uploading (24.04 noble ships ~1.75); the bundled SQLite in libsqlite3-sys needs
# only a C compiler, which build-essential (always present on builders) provides.
Build-Depends:
 debhelper-compat (= 13),
 cargo,
 rustc,
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://bulwark.nrl.ai
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/vietanhdev/bulwark.git
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/vietanhdev/bulwark
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: bulwarkctl
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
# ClamAV powers the optional antivirus scan; the rest of Bulwark works without it
# and prints a distro-aware install hint when it is absent. apt installs Recommends
# by default, matching the .deb produced by `cargo deb`.
Recommends: clamav
Description: Linux security misconfiguration & intrusion scanner (CLI)
 Bulwark scans a Linux host for security misconfigurations and intrusion
 indicators using a native Rust rule engine over declarative YAML rules, and
 explains findings in plain language with a suggested fix.
 .
 This package provides the command-line front-door, bulwarkctl. It can scan the
 local host or a remote machine over SSH, with no display session required, and
 covers configuration hardening, SSH, log analysis, and AI-assistant artifact
 checks. See the bulwark-app package for the desktop GUI.
